newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: NWE oil products dip as Iraqi crude emerges.
newsitem.headline: NWE oil products dip as Iraqi crude emerges.

text.p: NWE oil products dipped on Tuesday morning as Iraqi crude emerged, leading to slight futures weakness, dealers said.
Gas oil was down about $1 a tonne, the losses purely futures-related. Buyers were extremely cautious and still unwilling to pay Dec IPE screen flat or above.

High sulphur fuel oil was down about $2 a tonne, a single trading house selling at $115.25 and $115.50 fob ARA. Dealers said the trading house was interested in setting lower prices to suit an earlier cargo purchase. Later offers were at $116/$116.50.
